Movith Forms – SaaS Strategy Framework

Movith Forms is designed as a scalable multi-tenant SaaS platform.

All engineering decisions must support SaaS scalability.

Multi-Tenant Strategy

Each tenant:

Has logically isolated data

Has its own workflows

Has its own submissions

Has isolated configuration

Cannot access other tenant data

Rules:

All tenant-scoped entities must include TenantId.

All queries must enforce tenant filtering.

Background jobs must be tenant-aware.

Aggregations must respect tenant scope.

SaaS Growth Strategy

The platform must support:

Horizontal scaling

Feature gating (plan-based access)

Usage-based analytics

Performance monitoring

SLA-based service tiers

Future-ready design for:

Enterprise tenants

Mid-size companies

High-volume operational workflows

Product Scaling Principles

Features must be modular.

Aggregation logic must be reusable.

Dashboard data must be computed efficiently.

Read-heavy operations should be cacheable.

Performance must degrade gracefully under load.

Plan & Feature Gating Model

The system must support:

Free / Basic / Pro / Enterprise tiers (future-ready)

Feature flags per tenant

Rate limits per tenant

API usage tracking

SLA differentiation

No feature should assume universal availability.

SaaS KPI Awareness

The system must be capable of tracking:

Active tenants

Monthly active users

Submission volume

Workflow execution count

Error rate

SLA compliance

Health score per tenant

These KPIs are part of the core architecture and not afterthoughts.

Security & Governance Readiness

The SaaS strategy must be compatible with:

IAM integration

Role-based access control

Audit logging

Encryption at rest and in transit

Incident monitoring

Security is part of architecture, not an optional add-on.

Operational Maturity

The platform must evolve toward:

Insight-driven dashboards

Bottleneck detection

Performance anomaly detection

SLA breach monitoring

Automated risk alerts

The SaaS strategy prioritizes operational intelligence over cosmetic features.

Engineering Guardrail

If a proposed implementation:

Breaks tenant isolation

Introduces tight coupling

Moves business logic to UI

Ignores scalability concerns

Hardcodes plan logic

The agent must refuse and propose a compliant alternative.

All implementation decisions must align with SaaS scalability and governance.
